{"word":"ἀντερῶ","slug":"ἀντερῶ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀντερῶ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀντεῖπον'><el>ἀντεῖπον</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> with no <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> in use.\n<p/><i>to speak against, gainsay</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>τι πρός τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to refuse</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>οὐδὲν ἀντειρήσεται</el> no <i>denial shall be given</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}